Pre-commit hook: validates MYCELIUM_VERSION is present and semver-formatted when mycelium.sh is staged.
CI workflow: checks version string on every push, verifies tag matches script version on tagged pushes.

These enforce the versioning constraint note on the root tree (mycelium.sh find constraint → 'Versioning rules').

The three enforcement points:
1. Pre-commit hook: catches malformed versions before commit
2. CI version-present check: catches missing versions on push
3. CI tag-match check: catches tag/script mismatches on release
